0Rhodes%2C%20the%20Great%20Pyramid%20of%20Giza%2C%20the%20Hanging%20Gardens%20of%20Babylon%2C%20the%20Statue%20of%20Zeus%20at%20Olympia%2C%20the%20Temple%20of%20Artemis%20at%20Ephesus%2C%20the%20Mausoleum%20at%20Halicarnassus%2C%20and%20the%20Lighthouse%20of%20Alexandria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20only%20one%20of%20them%20is%20still%20standing%2C%20earthquakes%20and%20fires%20destroyed%20the%20other%20six.%20The%20Mausoleum%20of%20Halicarnauss%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20successive%20earthquakes%20between%20the%2011th%20and%2015th%20century%20CE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20heyday%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F297140%2Fwomen-queens-built-stepwells-india-architecture-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20monument%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20tomb%20of%20Mausolus%2C%20ruler%20of%20Caria%20(a%20region%20in%20present-day%20Turkey).%20But%20neither%20the%20devastating%20remains%20of%20stone%20it%20left%20behind%20nor%20the%20clouds%20of%20dust%20could%20erase%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20towering%20marble%20beauty%20that%20people%20would%20once%20gape%20at%20in%20pure%20wonder.%20The%20mammoth%20facade%20blended%20the%20ideas%20of%20Greek%20architects%20Pythius%20and%20Satyros%2C%20with%20sculptures%20flanking%20its%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20beauty%20personified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20palace%20on%20Muktaram%20Babu%20Street%20in%20North%20Kolkata%20(previously%20Calcutta%2C%20the%20seat%20of%20the%20British%20Raj)%2C%20is%20said%20to%20inspire%20the%20same%20reaction.%20While%20people%20have%20pointed%20out%20a%20resemblance%20between%20the%20Marble%20Palace%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20and%20the%20monument%20in%20Turkey%2C%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20any%20sound%20proof%20whether%20the%20latter%20inspired%20the%20former.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAn%20architectural%20emblem%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mansion%20that%20fuses